criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Subjects with Idiopathic Parkinson's Disease;

          -  Age > 18 years;

          -  Subjects should be in a positive therapeutic window or in the ON phase during the
             evaluations;

          -  Subjects must be able to walk at least 10 meters independently with or without any
             walking aid.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Not clinical stable subjects;

          -  SUbjects in OFF phase during the evaluations;

          -  Other neurological conditions (e.g. stroke, peripheral neuropathies, etc.);

          -  Other pathologies that can negatively influence the subject's walking ability (e.g.
             surgery at the lower limbs in the previous 6 months, important deformities at the
             lower limbs, etc.)
